His left leg often swells up," Gulbahar, who hails from Barkhal village in Assam's Marigaon district, told Al Jazeera.
As India struggles to contain the spread of the pandemic, families of more than 800 undocumented migrants being held indefinitely in six detention centres across Assam are worried about the safety of their loved ones.
Dozens of people have died inside the detention centres since 2009, the latest fatality occurring on Sunday.
Some of them are currently languishing in detention centres.
Trying for bailSome families are making desperate attempts to secure bail from the courts before the virus turns into a disaster inside the detention centres.